This module could be used either for:
1. Smooth transition from migrate tool to alembic
2. As standalone alembic tool

The following options are used by app internally:

_db_opts = [
    cfg.StrOpt('alembic_ini_path',
               default='',
               help=('Full path to alembic.ini file.')),
    cfg.StrOpt('migrate_repo_path',
               default='',
               help=('Full path to migrate_repo')),
    cfg.IntOpt('init_version',
               default=0,
               help='Initial database version.')
]

If you don't want to use migrate plugin with some project
just leave 'migrate_repo_path' set to an empty string.

Core points:
1. Upgrade/downgrade database with usage of alembic/migrate migrations
or both
2. Compatability with oslo.config
3. The way to autogenerate new revisions or stamps
